main event: An unidentified object was observed in the sky near Denver, Colorado on October 7, 1956.
interesting points: The object appeared to move very fast at an altitude of about 10,000 feet.
The object was observed for 20 seconds and was noted to the west-southeast.
The object moved in a zig-zag manner and disappeared, likely due to a meteorological variation or possible aircraft.
There were two similar sightings reported on September 23, 1956.
The weather conditions were clear and calm at the time of the sighting.
